The paper deals with face de-identification algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses privacy concerns and surveillance, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of human perceivers and deep convolutional neural networks suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of different algorithms, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current approaches and suggests future work, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
